message: I’m disgusted that a man who wanted to get away from the anarchy-tyranny of 1990s America would be labeled a “white supremacist”.
Removed him from a list he didn’t belong in.
Information on his page points to a paleoconservative, rather than white suoremacist,ideology.
Have not found any evidence on his page indicative of white supremacist leanings.
Have seen no evidence on his page linking him to white supremacist ideology.

It is unbelievable to me that someone would add Mr.Gadsden,a man who played a pivotal role in American history, to a list of American white supremacists and I’ve seen no evidence on his page detailing a connection to this sort of ideology.
/* Added back content and wikilinks on last edit */ Reply
Added more motivating ideologies.
Added the shootings to a list they belong to.
/* September 2022 */ Reply
Gypsies aren’t a race.
He hated Arabs and believed Jews to be superior.
There is no evidence he’s a white supremacist and is any more than a Christian extremist and terrorist.
I added information to the table included in the summary paragraph of the article.
At the time of the attack Breivik did not identify as a neo-Nazi and actually argued against the ideology in his manifesto.
